<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="281" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,620,645]" pageId="11" pageNumber="281">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[865,967,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="281">sentosus,</emphasis>
referring to the gnathos with dense tiny spines on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
